💗important shop update below💗
When we moved to bishop arts from our original location downtown just one year ago, I never thought I would be making a post about this again, but WE’RE MOVING! We spent the majority of the last year dealing with structural issues in our building, and got to the point where we had no choice but to find a new space. 

The silver lining is that we found a space that feels like it was always meant to happen. It’s cozy, has gated parking, outdoor patio areas, plenty of room for all of our artists, and space to continue to invite in others. Basically, this location has everything we currently offer, and then some. 

I’d be lying if I said this wasn’t an incredibly stressful chapter of my life. It would be easier to give up, to walk away, to abandon everything I’ve spent the past 3 years working towards as a business owner, but I’m so glad I stuck through it and figured out how to make this all work. I genuinely have poured my entire being into this studio not only because I love it so much, but because I feel it’s a space in this industry that’s important to offer. I take importance in offering a space that is inclusive of all clients and artists, and makes you feel safe and comfortable. A space where you know you will walk out with a quality tattoo and a positive experience no matter the service or artist who helps you. We aren’t perfect but we’ll do our best and make you laugh with all our silly jokes in the process. Because of all of this, I’d do this process over a million times.

All of our artists and piercers are still operating as normal, we all have our books open and are ready to help you with whatever we can. Our hours and appointments will all remain the same, the only thing changing is the location. Right now we are still operating in bishop arts at 224 Sunset for all appointments this week. Starting next week (Tuesday the 27th) we will be working at our new space, 2720 W mockingbird Ln. We hope that you all love this new space as much as we do, and invite you to celebrate this new beginning with us. Can’t wait to see ya there!!💗

💙Friday the 13th at Lady Magnolia💙 

We are hosting our Friday the 13th event this week and aim to offer you guys some cool tattoos, discounts on vintage and piercings, and celebrate our recent move into our new space! ✨ 

‼️We have partnered with @piercetheveil for this day and think this is the perfect group to help us put on this event! With the release of their new album, and our recent move, we’re joining together to celebrate some new beginnings! We have a flash sheet representing their most recent album release included in the slide above.♥️(They have teamed up with multiple shops in different areas for Friday the 13th events, so sorry they will not be performing)‼️

Our flash prices range from $100-$300, they are limited to 1 per person, arms and legs only so we can get to as many of you as possible. We will also be offering our get what you get options. The prices of those also range $100-$300. *Pricing includes black shading, your artist may have an added fee if you prefer color* 💙

Piercings will be $13 off the service fee and all vintage clothing will be 15% off! For all services and shopping, cash is best but we can accept card and other forms of payment as well.🤩

Doors open at 12:00 noon! We will keep an eye on the line throughout the day but if you need an idea of wait times you can always call the studio the day of! We will have our voicemail set up with FAQ and updates throughout the day. (Some of our past events we were able to accept walk ins all day, while some others we’ve had to cut off the line once we were full. We do have all of our artists working this event and will help as many people as we can!) 💞

We use an automated sign up system that texts you when you’re next in line, that way you’re able to leave the studio to go grab food or etc and come back for your service. Sign ups are done in person only in the order you arrive to the shop.💗 

As a reminder, we recently moved to 2720 W mockingbird ln and are so excited for you to see the new spot! Our parking is located in the big fenced in lot directly behind our building. Can’t wait to see you there!🤩

If y’all have been following since the beginning of Lady Magnolia’s founding year in 2020, y’all know that @brianaleflore signed our lease in our little downtown space weeks before Covid hit. When figuring out how to supplement tattoo income while we were closed down, Bri integrated her love for vintage clothing into Lady Magnolia in the form of a vintage clothing store. If you’ve followed the last couple of years, you’ve probably realized that we slowed down on posting the vintage clothing in order to make sure that our Instagram highlighted our artists’ work, jewelry and piercing, and didn’t look confusing on what we had to offer here. With our most recent move, we wanted to breathe life back into our vintage clothing store. We’ve decided to rebrand and seek a new business venture under the name Hold Steady Vintage, housed inside of Lady Magnolia Tattoo. Items sourced by our team @kaptainjkleiber @brianaleflore and @discountcowgirl who all have different areas of expertise, styles, and interests in what we offer through our inventory.

🖤🔥We will post here periodically, but for all new updates, a look at merchandise, and information on how to order from us online to have items shipped to you, follow us at @holdsteadyvintage owned and operated by @brianaleflore and @kaptainjkleiber 🔥🖤

♥️✨The goal of Lady Magnolia has always been to provide a space that’s comfortable for clients and artists, respect the history and hard work that came from those before us, and hire artists who do the same. Thank you @amandacampbellvisuals @jeremypopelevison @levisonproductions for sending over this clip from our interview we took back in the space in bishop arts, stay tuned for a new interview and content we’ll be shooting in our new space we just finished moving to! ✨♥️

Yesterday was the 3 year anniversary of Lady Magnolia’s first day open!! Our shop has been lucky enough to have shared our (three!!!) spaces with so many clients and artists, and I can say without a doubt that we would not be where we are today without all of you. In the past three years we have faced quite a few trials and tribulations as a studio, but have simultaneously had so much support from the community around us, and for that we are eternally grateful. We strive to be a space that is open and welcoming to all walks of life, and all styles of tattooing/piercing, while also adding value to the lives of those we are so lucky to be a small part of. These past three years have flown by so quickly and we can only hope to continue to grow and evolve over the next years to come! I’ll never take for granted the value and sustenance that this shop, our clients, and our community have added to my life. Thank you all for following, for coming in to the shop, for showing up to all of our events, and for supporting in all of the ways that you do. ❤️‍🔥🫶
